Appendix - FAQ

Configure card parameters and Deploy card

Configure card parameters that are displayed in SAP Build Work Zone

  1. Select the dt/configuration.js file (in the Explorer view on the left).

  2. Replace the content with the code below:

sap.ui.define(["sap/ui/integration/Designtime"], function (
    Designtime
) {
    "use strict";
    return function () {
        return new Designtime({
        "form": {
          "items": {
            "maxItems": {
              "manifestpath": "/sap.card/configuration/parameters/maxItems/value",
              "type": "integer",
              "label": "Maximum Items",
              "translatable": false,
              "description": "Defines how many items will be displayed at most."
            }
          }
        },
        "preview": {
          "modes": "LiveAbstract"
        }
      });
    };
});

Deploy Card

  1. Right-click on the manifest.json file (in the Explorer view on the left) and select the UI Integration Card:Package option from the dropdown menu.

This will generate a .zip file in your workspace panel.

  1. Once the file is generated right-click and choose Download to save it to a location on your computer.

  2. Return to Work Zone and access the Administration Console from the user actions dropdown menu under your avatar.

  3. Go to External Integrations > Business Content > Content Manager

  4. In the Content Manager, select Create and then click App

  5. On the New App screen click the Visualization tab, select UI Integration Card from the dropdown.

    Click Upload Card. Then select the .zip package you downloaded from Business Application Studio

  6. You will now see the details of the UI Integration Card you uploaded. Click Save and then return to the Content Manager overview.

  7. On the Content Manager overview screen locate the Everyone role (use the search box if necessary) and click on it to open the role editor

  8. Click Edit and then use the search box to locate your UI Card The Latest Sales Orders AC096819U21

  9. Once you have located your card click the toggle under Assignment Status to add it to the Everyone role and then click Save

Congratulations!

Now the basic UI5 card deployment is done.

To learn more about the Integration cards and their features, see the Card Explorer page.
